{
  "texts": [
    "The model learns topics by modelling word pairs in the whole corpus.",
    "BTM was developed on the background that a pair of words can reveal topics much better than a single word occurrence.",
    "The model assumes that two words will be assigned the same topic label if they have co-occurred.",
    "BTM received praise for capturing the global co-occurrences of words, however, the model was criticised for the strong assumption made as two co-occurring words may not mean the same topic label.",
    "Recently, the use of neural topic models is becoming popular (Wu et al. 2024)."
  ]
}